This paper is about multi-objective optimization algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes an efficient algorithm for the computation of the exact Expected Hypervolume Improvement (EHVI) for a generic case. EHVI is a criterion used in multi-objective Bayesian Global Optimization (MOBGO), which is a subfield of optimization algorithms commonly used in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
